## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Node.js 18+
- npm 9+
- Expo Go app on your phone ([iOS](https://apps.apple.com/app/expo-go/id982107779) / [Android](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=host.exp.exponent))

### Installation

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/redarbor-jobs.git

# Navigate to the project
cd redarbor-jobs

# Install dependencies
npm install --legacy-peer-deps
```

### Running the app

```bash
npx expo start
```

Then:
- **iOS**: Scan the QR code with your iPhone camera
- **Android**: Scan the QR code with the Expo Go app
- **iOS Simulator**: Press `i`
- **Android Emulator**: Press `a`

---

## API

This app consumes the public [Remotive API](https://remotive.com/api):

| Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|
| `GET /api/remote-jobs` | List of remote jobs |
| `GET /api/remote-jobs?search=` | Search by title or company |
| `GET /api/remote-jobs?category=` | Filter by category |
| `GET /api/remote-jobs?job_type=` | Filter by job type |
| `GET /api/remote-jobs/categories` | List of categories |

---

## Architecture Decisions

- **Zustand over Redux**: Simpler API, less boilerplate, perfect for this scale
- **Expo Router**: File-based routing keeps navigation predictable and scalable
- **NativeWind**: Utility-first styling speeds up UI development significantly
- **FlashList over FlatList**: Better performance for long job lists
- **AsyncStorage**: Lightweight persistence for favorites without a backend

